# Vite exposes only variables prefixed with VITE_
# https://vitejs.dev/guide/env-and-mode.html
#
# Copy to `.env` for local dev, or set these in Vercel → Environment Variables.

# --- Supabase (Project Settings → API) ---
# Use the project URL and the publishable (anon) key — never the service_role key in the frontend.
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
#
# Personal access token for Supabase CLI / CI (link, db push, secrets). Do NOT use VITE_ — never bundle in the browser.
# https://supabase.com/dashboard/account/tokens
SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN=
#
# Dashboard → Storage: bucket id must be `dog` (photos). Then run:
# supabase/migrations/20260429170000_storage_dog_bucket.sql
#
# --- PostHog (Product analytics) ---
# Project → Project API key (starts with phc_). Host: US https://us.i.posthog.com or EU https://eu.i.posthog.com
# Local CLI: npx -y @posthog/wizard@latest --integration react (requires interactive terminal; or use --ci --api-key phx_...)
VITE_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY=
VITE_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_HOST=https://us.i.posthog.com

# --- Stripe Payment Link ---
# VITE_STRIPE_PAYMENT_LINK=https://buy.stripe.com/...
VITE_STRIPE_PAYMENT_LINK=

# --- Confirmation page (/confirmation) after Stripe redirect ---
# Stripe Dashboard: success URL → https://YOUR_DOMAIN/confirmation

# --- Transactional email (Edge Function; not Vite env) ---
# Dashboard SMTP under Authentication only sends Auth emails. For app mail, deploy:
#   supabase link --project-ref YOUR_PROJECT_REF
#   supabase secrets set SMTP_HOSTNAME=... SMTP_PORT=465 SMTP_SECURE=true SMTP_USERNAME=... SMTP_PASSWORD=... SMTP_FROM="Letters From Your Dog <team@lettersfromyourdog.com>"
#   supabase functions deploy send-transactional-email
#
# Client: import { sendTransactionalEmail } from "./src/lib/sendTransactionalEmail.js";

# --- Stripe webhook (Edge Function `stripe-webhook`; not Vite env) ---
# Dashboard → Developers → Webhooks → Add endpoint:
#   https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co/functions/v1/stripe-webhook
#   Event: checkout.session.completed
# Then set secrets:
#   supabase secrets set STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_... STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_...
# Payment Link: enable “Collect customers’ addresses” (shipping) or shipping_* stays empty.
#
# --- Post-checkout welcome email (separate Edge Function; not Vite env) ---
# 1) Deploy: supabase functions deploy subscriber-welcome-email
# 2) Secret for the DB webhook (generate a long random string):
#   supabase secrets set SUBSCRIBER_WELCOME_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your-random-secret
# 3) Dashboard → Database → Webhooks: table public.subscribers, events INSERT + UPDATE
#    URL: https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co/functions/v1/subscriber-welcome-email
#    HTTP Headers: x-webhook-secret = same value as SUBSCRIBER_WELCOME_WEBHOOK_SECRET
# Uses the same SMTP_* secrets as send-transactional-email. Fires when a row becomes
# status active with a real email (Stripe checkout updates the existing subscriber row).
